Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Thinly slice the @tomatoes{2%medium}. Drain and slice the @mozzarella{1}. To make your Caprese salad, pop the tomato slices onto a large #plate{} and top each slice with mozzarella.

Pop the potato chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{} for the potatoes, sprinkle over the @Italian herbs{1/2%tsp} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer. > TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary. Once hot, roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Lay the @British chicken thighs{4} flat onto another baking tray. Drizzle with @olive oil{} then season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Spoon the @green pesto{1} equally between the chicken. Use the back of the #spoon{} to spread the pesto all over the top of each thigh. > IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Pop the baking tray onto the middle shelf of your oven and roast until browned and cooked through, ~{16-18%minutes}. > IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the potatoes and chicken thighs roast in the oven, take a little time to tidy up or put your feet up and relax. Once everything is cooked, remove from the oven and allow to rest for a few mins.

When everything is ready, pour the @olive oil{1%tsp} and @balsamic vinegar{6%ml} into a small #bowl{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Drizzle the balsamic dressing over the Caprese salad for those who'd like it. Divide the pesto chicken thighs, roast potatoes and Caprese salad between your plates. Enjoy!